Defendant Eric A Hair in court with attorney Robert J Hampton.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin with legal intern Renee Arndt.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 3 days time served.  Huber privileges for work and treatment.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.
Conditions:
*  Serve 30 days in the House of Correction with huber privileges for work and treatment; sentence to commence on July 1, 2016 by 5:00 pm;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate by agent;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Upon successful completion of probation, Court will grant expungement.
